ed decisions.Jeez, it’s like leaving your wallet on the counter at a restaurant.\nConfirm your trial: Once everything is set, ensure to confirm and finalize the registration through a verification email sent your way.\nFeatures of Jungle Scout During the Trial\nThis ensures users are working with the latest market trends, thus increasing their chances of success.\nKeyword Scout Tools\nAnother significant feature included in the trial is the Keyword Scout tool. This tool empowers users to uncover high-traffic keywords relevant to their products. It allows entrepreneurs to see what terms people are actually searching for on Amazon, which can make or break a product listing.\nUtilizing Keyword Scout can help refine product titles, descriptions, and backend keywords. By harnessing these tools during the Jungle Scout trial, users can make decisions grounded in solid analysis rather than intuition alone.\nBenefits of the Jungle Scout Day Trial\nThe Jungle Scout 7 Day Trial presents an impressive opportunity for individuals and businesses looking to elevate their e-commerce strategies. Furthermore, the Keyword Scout Tools help refine search terms, allowing users to discover what terms potential customers are actually using. This means one can align product offerings more closely with customer interests, a significant edge in e-commerce.\nUsers can track sales trends, inventory levels, and pricing models to see what works and what doesn’t. By digesting these insights, they’re better equipped to pivot their strategies effectively.\nMoreover, understanding competitor performance through...\nThis article section dives into how Jungle Scout stacks up against other leading tools like Helium 10 and Viral Launch. By assessing features, costs, and user feedback, users can make informed decisions that align with their business goals.\nJungle Scout vs. Helium\nWhen it comes to e-commerce tools, Jungle Scout and Helium 10 are like two heavyweight boxers, each bringing unique punches to the ring. Jungle Scout is widely recognized for its product research capabilities. While Jungle Scout is often praised for its user-friendly interface and deep product research features, Helium 10 might win in versatility, with tools that help beyond just finding the right product—think SEO optimization, financial analytics, and more. The critical question is, what aspect matters most to you? Whether it's seamless product research or multi-faceted support for an entire launch process can play a significant role in deciding which tools to invest in.\nJungle Scout vs. Viral Launch\nFocus: Jungle Scout is about product discovery, whereas Viral Launch emphasizes effective launches.\nData Insights: Jungle Scout often provides deeper sales data for products, important for long-term strategy.\nLearning Curve: Users generally report that Jungle Scout is easier to navigate, making it suitable for less experienced sellers.\nTo measure the outcomes of the Jungle Scout trial effectively, it's crucial to identify what success looks like. For many users, success can take various forms: accessing reliable product data, uncovering profitable niches, or simply gaining confidence in the tools they employ.\nConsider evaluating the following:\nDespite its strengths, there inevitably will be areas where the Jungle Scout trial might fall short. Recognizing these shortcomings can help fine-tune the platform's offerings, enhancing the user experience. Here are some common areas for potential improvement:\nOnboarding Process: Is the initial setup intuitive? If users struggle with navigating the platform or understanding how to exploit features, it's crucial to simplify this process.\nFeature Accessibility: Are all essential tools available during the trial, or is access limited, potentially hindering users from fully grasping the platform's capabilities?\nWhen it comes to subscription options for Jungle Scout, users have a handful of routes to consider. Understanding the choices available assists in making an informed decision geared toward your specific needs. Mainly, Jungle Scout offers tiers such as the Basic, Suite, and Professional plans. Evaluating which plan aligns with your future growth can save you a lot of hassle down the line. It’s worth mentioning that Jungle Scout often runs promotions that could impact these tiers, so keeping an eye on their website might yield some benefit.\nUnderstanding Pricing and Value\nOne significant element to take away is the depth of the features available in Jungle Scout. Each tool, from the Product Database to Keyword Scout, offers a unique angle that can enhance understanding of market dynamics. Entrepreneurs should not overlook the potential for these insights to shape crucial business strategies. Diverse Toolset: The variety of tools provided within the Jungle Scout ecosystem caters to various aspects of product research, ensuring comprehensive market analysis.\nLearning Opportunities: While the trial is designed to be user-friendly, each user may face unique challenges that can result in valuable learning experiences, adding to their skillset.\n\n\n--------\n搜索关键词：Jungle Scout UI interface design\n\n网页标题：Jungle Scout Web App New Feature Updates: New Design, Better Experience\n\n网页链接：https://www.junglescout.com/blog/web-app-feature-updates/\n\n发布时间：2018-03-19T00:00:00+08:00\n\n网页内容：![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/new-web-app.jpg)\nJungle Scout Web App New Feature Updates: New Design, Better Experience\nGreg Mercer\nMarch 19, 2018\nProduct Design , Product Features\nMaybe it’s that I am now settling into and decorating a permanent home after years traveling as a digital nomad, but I’ve been consuming a lot of HGTV. For those that aren’t familiar, they have a great show called Home Makeover where they totally change the look and feel of the home, but keep it’s strong foundation.\nWhy am I telling you about my newfound fascination with interior design?\nYou might have noticed the Jungle Scout Web App has had a makeover of it’s own. Same strong foundation, same benefits and value, just with a glossy new look and some very cool feature upgrades 🎉. We even solidified the foundation with some more accurate sales estimates, but more on that later….\nThis new design is focused on creating a more intuitive flow for users, and simplifying the user experience to help drive a faster and more efficient experience for finding and validating product ideas.\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Screen-Shot-2018-03-19-at-12.47.10-PM.png)\nJungle Scout Web App Redesign: The Background\nWe launched the Web App back in August of 2015, with the mission of helping people find and validate profitable products to sell on Amazon. Nothing has changed in our mission. But we have continued with laser-focus “behind the scenes”, in regards the product features and sales data estimates.\nSince our launch, we have also been continuing to collect your feedback, feature requests, and questions so that we could tie it together in a polished v2.0 of the Web App. So without further adieu, please let me take you on a brief tour….\n“This Product Database Filter Is Generating A TON of Gems… How Do I Save It For Later?”\nWhen you have stumbled upon a Product Database filter that works for you, you want to save it for future use. Until recently, this was not possible. Every time you logged into the Web App’s Product Database, you would have to re-set your categories.\nSo for example, suppose I wanted to investigate the market for over $15 that has a poor listing, yet still generate over 2000 unit sales per month. I might want to create a filter that looks something like this:\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/database-filter-set-1024x658.png)\nBut what if I want to have another product research session tomorrow looking at the same criteria for a different category? Well, now I can save the filter set, and just load it in the future!\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Saved-Filter-1024x685.png)\nThis is where I would name it. Notice that I am as specific as possible, including the Country (Marketplace), Categories, Price, Listing Quality Score, and other criteria that I used so I can easily remember what I used in the filter.\nThis is a feature that many of you have requested, and it is useful for building upon each product research session. I am so excited that it is now fully live!\nCreate Product Notes For More Thorough Research\nIf you’ve seen how I like to do Product Research, you know that I have a basic checklist that I like to go through. Here’s a post on how I found a killer product (bamboo marshmallow sticks). But when I was going through this process, I ended up taking a lot of notes, which were eventually scattered between various online notes, Google docs, spreadsheets, and more.\nWe have just built an easy way to create a unified log of notes on any product that you are tracking. Meet Product Notes, inside the Product Tracker. This is where you can add new notes in your Product Tracker:\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/add-product-tracker-notes-1024x675.png)\nWhen adding new notes, I find that it is helpful to categorize the note. You can also insert images (helpful if you have a screenshot that you want to add of a sample or a competitive product, for example).\nHere’s a look at some of these product notes within the product tracker:\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/product-notes-1024x685.png)\nGet Keyword Ideas With One Click\nWe have covered a lot about Amazon SEO and keyword research in the past. Here’s a good post of how I built an SEO-friendly listing for one of my products.\nBut how do you know which keywords you should target when putting your listing together? If you are paying for pay per click ads, you could dig in to your Search Term Report to see what people are searching for. This is a great methodology, if you currently have an active listing and can dig through actual search queries and advertising data.\nNot everyone has that luxury, especially if the product is not actually live yet. So we have the optimal solution for you: Keyword Clouds. In the Product Database, if you click on the ASIN, you can pull up the Keyword Cloud, which looks like this:\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/keyword-cloud-1024x703.png)\nThis is a really handy tool to use when you are crafting your listing, and you want to identify what some of the main keywords that you may want to consider including. This feature is pulling the most\nTo do this, I would add a few of the main competitors for my new product, and then pull up the Keyword Cloud. Are you including some of these keywords in your Title, Product Features, or Product Description? How about your backend keywords, to help Amazon identify what type of keywords you wish to rank for?\nNiche Hunter Keywords\nUsers with access to the Niche Hunter (Standard and Business Plan) can also pull up a Keyword Cloud along with some other Niche Data: Top Keywords, Niche Tips, and a Niche Opportunity Score. This is a look at how it looks in the app:\n![](https://www.junglescout.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/niche-hunter-keyword-cloud-1024x414.png)\nThis actually looks like a nice niche–10/10!\nWhere Are These Sales Estimates Coming From Anyway?\nGoing back to my HGTV thought earlier, there’s an important undercurrent to every house makeover: the value and integrity of a house is only as good as the foundation that it’s built upon. It doesn’t matter how pretty the outside of the house looks, if it is built on a shoddy foundation. The same applies to Amazon product research software…\nThe new features and updated design that I outline above are just the beginning of improving your product research as an Amazon seller. This redesign is the decoration on top of the strongest foundations – accurate sales estimates.\nIn fact, I can unabashedly make this statement: Jungle Scout has the most accurate Amazon sales estimates in the world! We have even given these estimates a special name: AccuSales™ .\nFor the past few years, we have focused on building the most robust algorithms to generate our sales estimates. The team includes a PhD-wielding Data Scientist, a Statistician, and multiple smart developers. They are working tirelessly behind the scenes of this new Web App design, ensuring that the algorithms are processing over 500 million data points collected every day with precision, and providing you with the most accurate estimates to fuel your business.\nWhat Should I Do Now?\nNow that you’ve had a brief tour of the new and improved Web App, I hope you get active leveraging these features to help uncover your next opportunity. What do you think of the new design and features? Please drop a comment below to share your thoughts! And if you have any other feature requests or feedback, we are all open to your feedback, email us support@junglescout.com!\n\n========\n搜索关键词：Helium 10 dashboard design\n\n网页标题：Your Guide to the Helium 10 Dashboard\n\n网页链接：https://amztoolset.com/helium-10-dashboard/\n\n发布时间：2025-06-10T00:00:00+08:00\n\n网页内容：Your Guide to the Helium 10 Dashboard\nJune 10, 2025\nBenjamin Williams\nThe Helium 10 dashboard is your Amazon business command center – a customizable hub where crucial sales data, keyword rankings, and growth insights live in one streamlined interface. It’s designed to accelerate decision-making and increase efficiency by delivering actionable insights, personalized recommendations, and the full power of Helium 10’s tool suite in one centralized view.\nGetting familiar with your dashboard isn’t just helpful – it’s essential for maximizing your Amazon success. Your Amazon Command Center\nThe Helium 10 dashboard is a customizable smart dashboard for e-commerce sellers and brands, and the ultimate Amazon seller dashboard. Think of it as mission control for your entire Amazon operation – everything you need to make data-driven decisions sits right at your fingertips.\nWith the introduction of Insights Dashboard, all these tasks are now intuitive and effortless with the most important data displayed as soon as you log in. You’ll see real-time sales performance, keyword rankings, competitor alerts, and growth opportunities without digging through complex reports.\nThe beauty lies in its integration capabilities. By integrating seamlessly with Helium 10’s full software suite, sellers can benefit directly from the synergy of all their favorite tools without having to bounce around to a dozen different pages or tabs. Instead, they can explore their favorite summaries from Profits, insights from Listing Analyzer, or updates from Keyword Tracker all from within the dashboard itself.\nHow to Access Your Dashboard\nAccessing your dashboard couldn’t be simpler. Once you log into your Helium 10 account, the dashboard appears as your main landing page – no searching required. It’s the first thing you’ll see, packed with widgets and data points tailored to your connected Amazon accounts.\nDon’t have a Helium 10 account yet? Your financial overview section delivers instant visibility into your business performance. In the center of the dashboard, there is a graphs section, which provides visual displays of your Revenue, Top Products, and Advertising. The Top Products tab shows a graph of your top products’ data for revenue, units sold, or refunds, and the Advertising tab shows your key advertising metrics, including Gross Revenue, PPC Spend, ACoS, and TACoS.\nYou’ll see today’s gross sales compared to yesterday’s performance, plus real-time order counts and units sold. This beats logging into Seller Central every few hours – your dashboard streams live data so you can spot trends instantly. When sales spike or dip unexpectedly, you’ll know within minutes instead of discovering it days later.\nThe Latest Orders widget shows your most recent transactions with product images, ASINs, prices, and timestamps. It’s like having a live ticker of your business activity, perfect for monitoring momentum throughout the day.\nKeyword Rank Monitoring\nThe “Your Tracked Keywords” section gives you a bird’s-eye view of your organic and sponsored keyword positions. You can toggle between ranking types and switch products to see which keywords are performing in the top 10 positions for each ASIN.\nThis real-time ranking data helps you spot ranking drops before they impact sales significantly. If a crucial keyword falls from page one to page three, you’ll see it immediately and can take corrective action through keyword optimization or increased PPC spending.\nThe dashboard also shows overall search volume for your tracked keywords, helping you prioritize which rankings matter most for your revenue goals.\nQuick Market Research Snippets\nThe Research a Keyword widget turns your dashboard into a mini research station. While it’s not a replacement for deep-dive tools like Magnet, it’s perfect for quick opportunity scouting or validating product ideas on the fly.\nEssential Connections \u0026 Shortcuts\nLinking Your Amazon Account\nConnecting your Amazon seller account unlocks the dashboard’s full potential. Your dashboard serves as the ultimate shortcut hub. Toward the bottom half of your dashboard, there is a section called “My Products.” This section brings in elements of multiple Helium 10 tools, including Helium 10 Ads, Chrome Extension, Alerts, Inventory Management, and several others. By bringing such a diverse array of features together into one section of the dashboard, you are able to laser focus on the performance indicators that matter most.\nThe top navigation bar provides quick access to major tools like Profits, Follow-Up, and Helium 10 Ads. The main “Tools” dropdown reveals the complete suite, organized by category for easy browsing.\nTool widgets at the bottom include brief descriptions – perfect for new users still learning each feature’s functionality and use cases.\nPersonalizing Your Dashboard Experience\nCustomizing Tool Layout\nWith a customizable view, you can filter your products list however you see fit. The tool widgets section allows you to rearrange tools by dragging and dropping them into your preferred order. Smart sellers put their most-used tools at the top for quicker access.\nYou can also group tools by workflow – product research tools together, then keyword research, then analytics. This creates logical pathways that match your daily routine, reducing clicks and mental overhead.\nThe “My Products” section offers extensive filtering options. With the ability to ‘star’ and ‘favorite’ ASINs, you can effortlessly prioritize your main product table to display only your preferred ASINs. This focus helps you concentrate on key products without getting distracted by your entire catalog.\nSetting Business Goals\nThe “Set a Goal for Gross Sales” widget adds accountability to your dashboard. Click “Get Started” to establish financial targets – whether you’re saving for vacation, planning business expansion, or working...\nStart with achievable goals to build momentum, then raise the bar as you consistently meet targets. This visual progress tracking creates powerful psychological motivation that many sellers find incredibly effective.\nDashboard Access Across Helium 10 Plans\nStart with the financial overview, then move to keyword tracking, followed by the tool shortcuts. This systematic approach prevents overwhelm and builds confidence.\nCreate bookmark shortcuts for your most-accessed dashboard sections. While everything’s available from the main view, direct links to specific widgets save precious seconds throughout your workday.\nSet up your workspace thoughtfully. Rearrange tool widgets to match your workflow, favorite your top-performing ASINs, and configure goal tracking for motivation. These personalizations compound over time, making your dashboard feel like a natural extension of your business operations.\nDon’t ignore the educational prompts. Is the Helium 10 Dashboard Easy to Use?\nAbsolutely. Helium 10 has invested heavily in user experience design, creating a dashboard that feels intuitive even for complete beginners. The learning curve is gentle – most sellers feel comfortable navigating within their first day of use.\nThe interface follows logical patterns. Financial data sits prominently at the top, tools are grouped by function, and important actions get highlighted with contrasting colors. Even complex features like Trendster integration feel accessible thanks to clean design and helpful tooltips.\nThe introduction of Helium 10’s Insights Dashboard is a major breakthrough for Amazon sellers and e-commerce brands. This all-in-one dashboard provides a centralized view of all your key metrics, plus personalized recommendations, actionable insights, and more to help you accelerate your decision-making, reduce manual tasks, and scale your business faster than ever.\n\n\n--------\n搜索关键词：Helium 10 dashboard design\n\n网页标题：January 2022\n\n网页链接：https://h10.com.cn/changelog\n\n网页内容：![](https://h10.com.cn/app/uploads/2021/01/helium-10-changelog-updates.jpg)\nJanuary 2022\n1/21/2022\nHelium 10 Chrome Extension Update:\nVersion 6.8.2 Released.\nThe Chrome Extension is now available in Chinese for all users.\nNew 2022 US FBA fulfillment fee changes updated in Profitability Calculator.\nMWS Connection Button allows users to connect their Amazon and Helium 10 accounts.\nListing Builder Update:\nFrom the Helium 10 dashboard, users can spin the Pinterest Trends Widget to see what’s trending on that site, then deepen their research using the Helium 10 research tools to find new product ideas.\nDecember 2021\n12/1/2021\nThe Helium 10 Amazon Anomaly Tracker launches\nHelium 10 members can sign up for email notifications whenever a new, broad anomaly is detected.\nNovember 2021\n11/30/2021\nListing Builder Update\nSellers can build or optimize Amazon listings using the new Helium 10 Listing Builder software.\nListings can be synced directly to Seller Central.\nListing Builder gathers and organizes researched keywords by search volume and frequency.\nAs users build a listing, the software’s listing analysis component scores the listing’s effectiveness.\n11/29/2021\nHelium 10 Chrome Extension Update\nJapan Marketplace added. All users can research products on amazon.co.jp using the Helium 10 Extension.\n11/16/2021\nBlack Box Update\nUsers can filter product search results by Title Density in Black Box Keywords and title keywords in Black Box Niche.\nAmazon Marketplace Update\nUsers can research products and keywords in Amazon Japan using Black Box, Cerebro, Magnet and Trendster.\nOctober 2021\n10/12/2021\nHelium 10 Mobile App\nHelium 10 for Walmart: Profits, Cerebro, Magnet and the Helium 10 Extension\nWalmart 3rd party sellers can connect their Walmart Seller Accounts to their Helium 10 Account.\nThe Helium 10 Extension allows users to actively research products on Walmart.com.\nUsers can research keywords on Walmart using Magnet and Cerebro.\nWalmart 3rd party sellers can track their financial data using Profits.\nHelium 10 Chrome Extension\nChrome Extension 6.6.0 now supports Walmart.\n8/17/2021\nHelium 10 Chrome Extension\nChrome Extension 6.5.0 now supports product and keyword research for Amazon’s Australian marketplace.\n8/4/2021\nCerebro and Magnet Update\nCerebro and Magnet allow users to filter for, and to see, the number of page one products that include a searched keyword in their product title. Results appear in the new Title Density and Headline ASIN columns.\nJuly 2021\n7/30/2021\nHelium 10 Mobile App Update\nUsers can easily save mobile-researched products and their keywords to their Helium 10 account’s My List.\nHelium 10 Dashboard Update\nThe Mega Menu features a drop-down navigation menu, including the ability to change your personal layout to foreground seven frequently used tools for rapid access.\nMy List is now organized into My List – Products and My List – Keywords.\n7/13/2021\nHelium 10 Site\nThe Helium 10 docu-series Elevate premieres, exploring the seller’s journey. Users can watch each episode when it airs, via the Resources menu on the Helium 10 website or on the Helium 10 YouTube channel.\nHelium 10 Membership\nThe exclusive Helium 10 Serious Sellers Club opens and begins accepting applications from subscribers who have reached revenue milestones in their Amazon business.\n7/12/2021\nHelium 10 Dashboard\nElite and Diamond members can monitor their current and past Adtomic ad spend from their billing page, which can be accessed via the dashboard.\n7/6/2021\nPortals Update\nUsers can search for and purchase domains for their active landing pages inside Portals.\nChrome Extension Update\nRedesigned Review Insights opens into an overview window with helpful filters, analysis, and a review graph.\nJune 2021\n6/14/2021\nHelium 10 CPR Formula\nStarter and Free Helium 10 users can now create an active Portal and collect data from up to 100 customer visits.\n6/3/2021\nHelium 10 Website Update\nHelium 10 launches its Trusted Partner Directory, where sellers can find the external resources and services they need to run their Amazon business. The directory exclusively lists vendors and experts with whom Helium 10 maintains an ongoing, professional relationship.\nHelium 10 Software Launch: Audience\nAudience provides Helium 10 users the ability to poll Amazon shoppers about their preferences on images, copy, and product ideas. Learn how to set up your first poll.\n6/2/2021\nHelium 10 Dashboard Update\nPlatinum, Diamond, and Elite members who have active MWS tokens, but have not yet activated Review Request automations, will see a prompt on their dashboards allowing them to set up Request a Review automations in two simple clicks.\nApril 2021\n4/20/2021\nChrome Extension Update\nBlack Box, Magnet, Cerebro, Keyword Tracker, Market Tracker, and Trendster are all available/supported in the Australian marketplace.\n4/14/2021\nHelium 10 Two-Factor Authentication\nTwo-factor authentication is available for all Helium 10 users, regardless of account type.\nIdentifies shared keywords, shared top 10 keywords, shared total search volume, shared top...\nInventory Manager splits from Profits into a stand-alone tool. Users can access it under the Operations section of the Helium 10 dashboard.\n3/2/2021\nBlack Box Update\nUsers can limit search results for products using the Include Seller and/or Exclude Seller filters.\n3/1/2021\nChrome Extension Update\nChrome Extension 5.2.Helium 10 creates a helpful onboarding checklist for new users, to guide them through setting up their account and using the tools for the first time.\n1/20/2021\nChrome Extension Update\nChrome Extension allows users to research Alibaba suppliers while on Amazon.The Save Filters button and Filter Library button allow users to save and access a set of search criteria for future product searches. Read the tutorial in the Knowledge Base.\n11/6/2020\nHelium 10 Dashboard Update\nUsers can submit feature requests using the ‘?’ drop-down menu link “Share your ideas.”\n\n\n--------\n搜索关键词：Helium 10 dashboard design\n\n网页标题：Helium 10 Review (2025) – Should You Buy? (My Verdict)\n\n网页链接：https://www.demandsage.com/helium-10-review\n\n网页内容：Helium 10 is a powerful Amazon seller suite for established sellers and private-label merchants.\nIt offers a free version that allows you to assess some of its features on the go.\nHelium 10 offers a pinpoint accuracy of 79.3% compared to its predictions and sales estimates with actual Seller Central data.\nHelium 10’s Chrome extension is a handy tool for existing sellers who are looking to extract money keywords and product ideas while casually browsing the Amazon marketplace.\nWho Is Helium 10 For?\nHelium 10 is built for businesses of any size. But ideally, sellers with high sales volu